originalText.text:
I am writing to express my disappointment about my recent experience at Tammy's on Tuesday, 1/24/24, where I experience your lash service for the first time.

I initially requested the $22 classic lashes; however, when it came time to pay, I was informed the service would cost $30. This discrepancy was surprising, as I had clearly communicated my preference for the $22 option.

Moreover, the quality of the lash service was unsatisfactory. The lashes began falling off overnight, and by Wednesday, most had come off. I returned to Tammy's on Wednesday to request a refund, but unfortunately, I was informed that refunds are not provided. Instead, I was offered a redo of the service or an alternative service, such as eyebrow threading.

I must express my disappointment not only with the service itself but also with the customer service provided by your staff. The lack of transparency in pricing and the unwillingness to address my concerns with a refund were disheartening. Additionally, the suggestion of an alternative service felt dismissive, especially given the subpar experience I had.

I believe in constructive feedback and hope that my concerns can be addressed promptly. I would appreciate your assistance in resolving this matter, whether through a refund or a more satisfactory reevaluation of the lash service.

I value the ambiance of Tammy's and hope that improvements can be made in the customer service department to ensure a more positive experience for future clients.

Thank you for your attention to this matter

originalText.text: I used to love Tammy’s but the staff person closest to the window is extremely rude and talks to people nastily. I explained what I wanted and she shut me down and said no without trying to listen to what I wanted done. Which is fine you can deny service to whomever but I went to Cinderella Eyebrows on 125th they listened and executed the same thing I asked for. I will NOT be returning to Tammy’s to spend my money with people that lack customer service.

originalText.text: I heard about Tammys from my cousin.I had admired her long eyelashes and asked where she got them done at. She told me and I just loved the way they looked I called to set up an appointment with Tammy. It is really nice and clean establishment and Tammy and the whole staff was really sweet.  It was my first time getting eyelashes extensions. Im glad I got them done because it has made such a huge difference!!! It is money well spent. I love my lashes and she clearly know what she is doing!!!!

originalText.text: Tammys is the best place to go for a wax and eyebrow. Her services are amazing and the family run business made us feel at home and comfortable. I am happy to have this family run business in our community. I would recommend anyone who asks for eyebrow or wax services to go to Tammy’s. I have not tried any other service provided but I am sure they would be as excellent as the services I received. Thank you Tammy and family for your amazing customer service. I am a customer for life alone with my daughter and anyone else I will send to your Spa.
